Here's an implementation of the "ReverseLetters" function in MATLAB that reverses the sequence of letters between the first and last letter of the input word:

function sout = ReverseLetters(sin)
    % ReverseLetters takes an input phrase consisting of a single word
    % and reverses the sequence of letters between the first letter and 
    % last letter. The input phrase could be a character vector of any length.

    % Convert the input word to a character array
    chars = char(sin);

    % Get the first and the last letter of the word
    firstLetter = chars(1);
    lastLetter = chars(end);

    % Reverse the sequence of letters between the first and last letter
    middleLetters = reverse(chars(2:end-1));

    % Combine the reversed letters to form the output word
    sout = [firstLetter, middleLetters, lastLetter];
end

Apologies for the omission. Here's the updated implementation that handles the case when the input word consists of only one letter:

function sout = ReverseLetters(sin)
    % ReverseLetters takes an input phrase consisting of a single word
    % and reverses the sequence of letters between the first letter and 
    % last letter. The input phrase could be a character vector of any length.

    % Convert the input word to a character array
    chars = char(sin);

    % Check if the input word consists of only one letter
    if length(chars) == 1
        % If it does, then the output is the same as the input
        sout = sin;
    else
        % Get the first and the last letter of the word
        firstLetter = chars(1);
        lastLetter = chars(end);

        % Reverse the sequence of letters between the first and last letter
        middleLetters = reverse(chars(2:end-1));

        % Combine the reversed letters to form the output word
        sout = [firstLetter, middleLetters, lastLetter];
    end
end

Here's the implementation of the "PrintGreeting" function in MATLAB:

function welcomeMessage = PrintGreeting(userName)
    % PrintGreeting inserts the text "Greetings", followed by a single space,
    % and then a name, given by the string scalar userName.

    % Construct the welcome message by concatenating the strings
    welcomeMessage = "Greetings " + userName;

    % Print the welcome message
    disp(welcomeMessage);
end
